{"questionId":"13290","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Three points in three-dimensional space have coordinates A(0, 0, 2), B(0, 2, 0) and&nbsp;C(3, 1, 0).</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the vector&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\overrightarrow {{\\text{AC}}} \">\n  <mover>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>AC</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>→</mo>\n  </mover>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\overrightarrow {{\\text{AC}}} = \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}} 3&nbsp;\\\\  1&nbsp;\\\\   { - 2}  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mover>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>AC</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>→</mo>\n  </mover>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>Accept row vectors or equivalent.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13290","referenceCode":"19M.1.AHL.TZ2.H_2a.ii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the vector AC → .","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.12—Vector definitions","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.16—Vector product"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}